<br>
Megaera was the best out of the trio, she had just come from another meeting with Bellerophon. Tisiphone was still a little pissed at the Victory Goddess and without Mojo around to talk to, she kept her anger inside.<br>
<br>
Alecto had just come back from Ares Temple after a little meeting with the other Gods where yet another male had fallen for the Goddess of Love.<br>
&quot;How typical.&quot; She growled lightly.<br>
<br>
Megaera sighed.<br>
&quot;Yeah well get over it. You could have almost any dark God on Olympus.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alecto stood up growling, &quot;Well what if I am tired of the dark Gods?&quot; She folded her arms and sighed leaning up against the wall while her sisters sat still in their thrones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 12:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Curiosity killed the cat...well will it get Apollo killed?</span><hr size=1> The golden god of light's sandels clapped against the marble stairs at the entrance of the Furies temple. His midnight blue toga ruffeled about, with all of his trimmings in gold. His crystal blue eyes wandered around the temple. He noticed many priests and what not running about preparing things. They all stopped and hit the floors as Apollo made his presence known by caughing.<br>
<br>
&quot;Please...stand.&quot; he doesn't even make eye contact with them, and with a roll of his wrist he dismisses them. 'I grow so tiresome of all these airhead mortals dropping to the floor everytime I show up.' he thought to himself. He made his way through the hallways and corridors until he found the room where the Furies were retiring.<br>
<br>
&quot;Good evening ladies.&quot; he said with his dazzaling smile. His eyes bounced from goddess to goddess until he found Alecto, who looked rather purturbed. 'Just as I thought, Ares has got another victem.' he says to himself.<br>
<br>
&quot;Umm, I saw that little...::he pauses::...display made by my brother. I  wish to apologize for him as I know that he himself would never do as such. I just came over, as I was making my way to my temple in the eastern sky which is on the way, to make sure that you were ok, which you are obviously not.&quot; Apollo, very bluntly sat down next to her, shaking the hair from his eyes. He sat back resting his weight on his arms.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
