&quot;Come on Tisiphone, let's go see how the priests are doing with the sacrifices.&quot;<br>
Tisiphone nodded and stood looking to her sister.<br>
As Megaera passed Apollo she whispered, &quot;Never touch a burning flame.&quot;<br>
Speaking of her sister's anger of course.<br>
<br>
Seeing that her sister's had left her there, Alecto stormed back to her throne and sat herself upon it. She looked at Apollo as if hiding something. &quot;I am fine Apollo, Ares and I have a certain relationship. You know, get our kicks without any attachments.&quot; She smirked, a burning still in her eyes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 12:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Never touch a Burning Flame</span><hr size=1> Apollo took note of the sisters warning. His eyes sort of bulged at Alecto's comment. As it registered in his mind, his nose wrinkled and his face showed disdain.<br>
<br>
&quot;I understand that one must get one's...&quot;kicks&quot; as you call it. But with Ares? Of all the divinities upon Olympus? C'mon Alecto, you can do better without trying! Ares such a, such a, bohemith! To do anything of meaning with him is simply opprobrius! Yes I make, mistakes of such kind, but I would never...::he eyes show that he is searching for the word::...lower, or demean myself by doing it with such a unit. If you know what I am talking about.&quot; He shrieks, and shudders as he even gives it a thought.<br>
<br>
He walks over to a table, and pours himself a glass of nectar. He sips it and looks up at Alecto, shaking the hair from his sparkling eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;When your getting your ::he hesitates, not liking the choice of words:: &quot;kicks&quot; with Ares, you are surely imagining yourself with someone else, verdad? Am I correct? One would surely hope so. But what Apollo wants to know is who?&quot; he smiles and burries his nose into his glass. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 1:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> &quot;Kicks&quot;</span><hr size=1> Alecto sighed as she got yet another lecture about Ares. No, no one ever spoke with Megaera about Cupid or Dionysus.<br>
<br>
She sighed.<br>
&quot;Well Apollo, you would be able to say that. But I as a Furie am not. For you see, when all the other male Gods are flaunting themselves over Dite, Artemis and Persephone, I am here having to settle for Gods like Ares.&quot; <br>
<br>
Decides not to mention the mortals.<br>
<br>
&quot;And what do you care who I think about? It doesn't matter to you. Nothing of me concerns any of the Gods.&quot;<br>
<br>
She walked over and poured herself a chalice of nectar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 1:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Apollo does not FLAUNT...do I?</span><hr size=1> Apollo gave Alecto a look before taking a breath. He placed his hand upon his chest and said:<br>
<br>
&quot;The great Apollo does not FLAUNT...do I?&quot; he said, or rather asked. A bit of question was in his eye. He knew that he showed himself off, but did he fault around like perhaps his father? 'Ofcourse not Apollo, you are nothing like your father!' he thought to himself.<br>
<br>
&quot;And I was just asking about who you imagined, I was making conversation. Because you know who I have a thing for I was just trying to take a peek into Alecto's world. And I do care, about everyone, cuz in one way or another, everyone cares about me.&quot; He said, his arrogant side flaring up.<br>
<br>
He sipped his nectar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 1:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Touchy. . .</span><hr size=1> She smirked. A Furie always got a thrill out of getting to people, especially Gods. And even though she didn't want to upset Apollo, seeing him get angry for a brief moment gave her chills.<br>
