&quot;Goodevening.&quot; he nods to her and turns as he hears the loud shrieks of Alecto.<br>
<br>
&quot;No  Alecto, you obviously cannot be open enough to talk about yourself truthfully. And I as the god of truth will not stand here and be left in a shroud of untruth! And I am not still here I was JUST LEAVING!!&quot; Apollo hollared and stormed for the exit. He turned quickly as his foot hit the first step and he hissed:<br>
<br>
&quot;I came here because I cared. Is it so hard to believe that someone actually cares!? I saw you were hurt and I thought that perhaps I could do something!! Damn, try and help someone these days...&quot; he muttered and stormed out. He tripped, but caught himself. He shrieked and moaned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ugh!&quot; he said as he walked off trying to retain his dignity. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 1:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Closing. . </span><hr size=1> Alecto threw her hands up and the doors shut before Apollo had a chance to leave. As he turned to face her, she looked calm and a bit saddened. Almost. . . mortal.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why do you care?&quot; She muttered softly.<br>
<br>
&quot;Most others have better things to do than to care about a Furie.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 2:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fruits of effot...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Like I said before, I care about everyone because everyone in a way cares about me. And it would be selfish and wrong of me not to care in return. You looked hurt and I wanted to help. And no I do not have anything better to do. No god does really.&quot;<br>
<br>
He looked over to her his eyes shimmering in the moonlight, his hair swayed as a breeze ran through the temple. In that instant if he was not a god, he would of certainly looked like one, if he was not already blindingly beautiful, he would be...in that instant. It was perhaps when he was at work ain his &quot;people skills&quot; that he looked his best. And he was certainly working hard at breaking Alecto open so that he may reap the fruits of his effort.<br>
<br>
&quot;So please, if you are not going to talk. Let me go, I will go be with my sister or someone. Anyone who will talk, willingly.&quot; his face was filled with empathy, the golden god shone in every aspect of the word. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 2:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Letting go of bitterness. . .</span><hr size=1> Alecto sighed hearing this. She usually loved having people angry, it gave her a thrill. But seeing Apollo upset at her made her feel weak, and she did not like that feeling.<br>
<br>
&quot;Come back in Apollo, we can talk.&quot;<br>
<br>
She lowered her head wondering why she was giving into him. She had never done that before.<br>
<br>
She sighed lightly to herself as she walked back to the throne room sitting down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 2:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The smile that can turn the world on its side...</span><hr size=1> And with those words, the few words Alecto said Apollo smiled. He smiled, with his smile that could turn the world on its side. His smile seemed to illuminate the night. He shook the hair from his eyes and followed Alecto back into her throne room. His sandles clapping against the marble floor as he goes. He couldnt help but wonder what made her change her mind.<br>
<br>
He tossed his hair again as he took a seat on the floor. This gave a hint to how young at heart he actually was, how innocent he was. Here he is in a room full of elaborate sofas and what not and he chooses to sit on the floor. He folds his legs indian style.<br>
<br>
&quot;So?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamphitritegoddessofthesea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amphitrite Goddess of the Sea</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_cyanspot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 2:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letting go of bitterness. . .</span><hr size=1> ::Amphitrite through all this, sits there listening. And thinking about their words. When they both come back she feels that this is not her place even though she does care. She frowns and gets up and walks to the door.:: <p><BR>~*Amphitrite*~ <BR>Queen of the Sea</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/utheerinyes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Erinyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(6/28/01 2:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> So. . .</span><hr size=1> She sighed having never told anyone this before.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think of someone kind, loving, someone who knows how to treat a Goddess.&quot;<br>
<br>
As she talked she sort of went off into her own world.<br>
<br>
&quot;Someone with a heart, someone who can please me in every way imaginable.&quot;<br>
<br>
She began twirling a strand of her wild blonde hair around her finger.<br>
<br>
&quot;Someone. . . &quot; Sighs. . &quot;Someone who isn't Ares.&quot;<br>
<br>
She snapped out of it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=90.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showMessageRange?topicID=90.topic&start=41&stop=51>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showPrevMessage?topicID=90.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showNextMessage?topicID=90.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=90.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.emailToFriend?topicID=90.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.threadControl?topicID=90.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/deleteThread.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=90.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=90.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of re